    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large dry pan over a medium heat</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your<strong> pine nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tagliatelle</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to blister</p><p>Tip: Squash the tomatoes with the back of a spoon to release their juices!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have blistered, add your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>sliced garlic</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) to the pan with the <strong>drained tagliatelle</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and a generous splash of <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy tomato sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle-and-toasted-pine-nuts/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy tomato sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
